---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Custom Lead Frames & Stamped Leadframes | High Precision Manufacturing"
  description="Kravzik manufactures high precision stamped lead frames and leadframes for semiconductor IC packaging. IATF 16949 certified, plus-minus 0.002mm tolerance, 1500+ SPM. Custom lead frames for automotive, telecom, medical."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-navy-900 text-white py-20">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-accent text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Products / Lead Frames</p>
        <h1 class="text-white mb-4">High Precision Stamped Lead Frames</h1>
        <p class="text-steel-300 text-lg leading-relaxed">
          Coplanarity-critical custom lead frames for semiconductor IC packaging. Manufactured to sub-micron precision in our IATF 16949 certified facility, with 100% burr-free micro-hole perforation at speeds exceeding 1500 SPM.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Overview -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h2 class="mb-4">What Is a Lead Frame?</h2>
        <p class="text-steel-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          A lead frame is a thin metal plate to which semiconductors are attached during the device assembly process. Also called a <strong class="text-steel-500">leadframe</strong>, this thin-layered metal component connects the wiring from tiny electrical terminals on the semiconductor surface to the large-scale circuitry on printed circuit boards and electronic devices.
        </p>
        <p class="text-steel-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          As a <strong class="text-steel-500">lead frame manufacturer</strong>, quality is the defining parameter. Any microscopic defect — edge deformation, burr formation, or coplanarity deviation — can adversely impact semiconductor adhesion and render the greater assembly inoperable.
        </p>
        <p class="text-steel-400 leading-relaxed">
          Our <strong class="text-steel-500">stamped lead frames</strong> are engineered to eliminate these risks through advanced progressive die tooling, real-time in-die vision inspection, and precision process control at every stage of production.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Capability Metrics -->
  <section class="py-12 bg-steel-100/50">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-6 text-center">
        {[
          { value: '+/- 0.002mm', label: 'Tolerance Control' },
          { value: '1500+ SPM', label: 'Stamping Speed' },
          { value: '100% Burr-Free', label: 'Edge Quality' },
          { value: '0.10mm', label: 'Min Material Thickness' },
        ].map(m => (
          <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-lg border border-steel-200/50">
            <div class="text-2xl font-extrabold text-accent mb-1" set:html={m.value} />
            <div class="text-xs font-medium text-steel-400 uppercase tracking-wider">{m.label}</div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Applications -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="mb-10 text-center">Lead Frame Applications by Industry</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {[
          {
            industry: 'Semiconductor',
            desc: 'IC lead frames for device packaging across the semiconductor ecosystem.',
            items: 'QFN leadframes, SOIC leadframes, QFP leadframes, DIP leadframes, BGA leadframes, Optocoupler leadframes, ASIC leadframes',
          },
          {
            industry: 'Automotive EV & E-Mobility',
            desc: 'Power module and control system leadframes for next-generation electric vehicles.',
            items: 'IGBT module leadframes, MOSFET leadframes, Power module leadframes, ECU leadframes, LiDAR sensor leadframes, Inverter leadframes',
          },
          {
            industry: 'Telecommunications',
            desc: 'High-frequency leadframes for RF and optical communication systems.',
            items: 'RF module leadframes, Optical transceiver leadframes, Base station leadframes, Router leadframes, Antenna leadframes',
          },
          {
            industry: 'Consumer Electronics',
            desc: 'Miniaturized leadframes for compact consumer devices.',
            items: 'SMD LED leadframes, LED bracket leadframes, Display driver leadframes, Camera sensor leadframes, Wearable device leadframes',
          },
          {
            industry: 'Medical & Healthcare',
            desc: 'Precision leadframes for life-critical medical devices and implantables.',
            items: 'Pacemaker IC leadframes, Biosensor leadframes, Hearing aid leadframes, Ultrasound leadframes, Implantable device leadframes',
          },
          {
            industry: 'Industrial & Machinery',
            desc: 'Robust leadframes for demanding industrial control environments.',
            items: 'Motor drive leadframes, PLC controller leadframes, Industrial relay leadframes, Power supply leadframes',
          },
        ].map(app => (
          <div class="p-6 bg-steel-100/50 rounded-lg border border-steel-200/50">
            <h3 class="text-lg mb-2">{app.industry}</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-steel-400 mb-3">{app.desc}</p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5">
              {app.items.split(', ').map(item => (
                <span class="inline-block px-2.5 py-1 text-xs bg-white border border-steel-200 rounded text-steel-500">{item}</span>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Critical Risks & Solutions -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-navy-900">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-white mb-4 text-center">Critical Risks in Lead Frame Stamping</h2>
      <p class="text-steel-400 text-center mb-12 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Each risk below is identified, quantified, and mitigated through our engineered stamping solutions — not through post-process inspection alone.
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {[
          {
            risk: 'Coplanarity Deviation',
            impact: 'Non-flat leadframes cause die attach failure, wire bonding misalignment, and package warpage during molding.',
            solution: 'Precision-guided stripper plates with micro-adjustable die clearance. In-die coining stations that stress-relieve the strip before final blanking. Continuous laser flatness measurement at 100% inspection rate.',
          },
          {
            risk: 'Micro-Burr Formation',
            impact: 'Burrs exceeding 10 microns disrupt wire bonding, create short circuits, and contaminate cleanroom assembly environments.',
            solution: 'Ultra-fine-grain tungsten carbide tooling with polished cutting edges maintained to sub-micron sharpness. Progressive die stations with dedicated burr-suppression geometry at each cutting operation.',
          },
          {
            risk: 'Edge Deformation & Micro-Cracking',
            impact: 'Stressed edges lead to lead bending during trim/form operations and latent field failures under thermal cycling.',
            solution: 'Optimized punch-to-die clearance ratios per material thickness. Radius-controlled cutting edges with multi-stage shaving stations that progressively refine the sheared surface.',
          },
        ].map(item => (
          <div class="p-6 bg-navy-800 rounded-lg border border-navy-700">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3">
              <span class="w-3 h-3 bg-accent rounded-full shrink-0"></span>
              <h3 class="text-white text-base">{item.risk}</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-steel-400 leading-relaxed mb-1">
              <span class="text-steel-500 font-semibold text-xs uppercase tracking-wider">Impact: </span>
              {item.impact}
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-steel-400 leading-relaxed">
              <span class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-xs uppercase tracking-wider">Solution: </span>
              {item.solution}
            </p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Engineered Alloys -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-center">Engineered Alloys for Lead Frame Packaging</h2>
      <p class="text-steel-400 text-center mb-12 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Material selection directly determines electrical conductivity, thermal dissipation, and mechanical integrity. Our inventory covers the full spectrum of leadframe-grade alloys.
      </p>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b-2 border-steel-200">
              <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-xs font-semibold text-navy-900 uppercase tracking-wider">Alloy</th>
              <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-xs font-semibold text-navy-900 uppercase tracking-wider">Composition</th>
              <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-xs font-semibold text-navy-900 uppercase tracking-wider">Conductivity (% IACS)</th>
              <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-xs font-semibold text-navy-900 uppercase tracking-wider">Tensile Strength</th>
              <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-xs font-semibold text-navy-900 uppercase tracking-wider">Primary Application</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-steel-200/50">
            {[
              { alloy: 'C19400', comp: 'Cu-Fe-P', cond: '65', strength: '450-550 MPa', app: 'General-purpose IC leadframes, consumer electronics' },
              { alloy: 'C70250', comp: 'Cu-Ni-Si-Mg', cond: '43', strength: '650-750 MPa', app: 'High-strength power module leadframes, automotive' },
              { alloy: 'Alloy 42', comp: 'Fe-42Ni', cond: '3', strength: '550-650 MPa', app: 'Low-expansion leadframes for ceramic packages' },
              { alloy: 'C18150', comp: 'Cu-Cr-Zr', cond: '80', strength: '480-560 MPa', app: 'High-conductivity power semiconductor leadframes' },
              { alloy: 'C10200', comp: 'OFHC Copper', cond: '101', strength: '220-280 MPa', app: 'Ultra-high conductivity applications, RF leadframes' },
            ].map(alloy => (
              <tr class="hover:bg-steel-100/50">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-semibold text-navy-900">{alloy.alloy}</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-steel-500">{alloy.comp}</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-steel-500">{alloy.cond}</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-steel-500">{alloy.strength}</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-steel-500 text-xs">{alloy.app}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Post-Stamping -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-steel-100/50">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-center">Post-Stamping & Plating Capabilities</h2>
      <p class="text-steel-400 text-center mb-12 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Leadframe functionality depends on surface finish. Our in-house plating and coating lines ensure consistent deposit thickness and adhesion.
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
        {[
          { title: 'Silver Plating', desc: 'Spot and overall silver plating for wire bond pads. Controlled thickness from 1.5 to 6.0 microns with 100% XRF verification.' },
          { title: 'Nickel-Palladium Plating', desc: 'Ni/Pd/Au pre-plated leadframes (PPF) eliminating post-assembly solder plating. Superior solderability without whisker risk.' },
          { title: 'Selective Plating', desc: 'Precision stripe and spot plating on continuous reel-to-reel lines. Minimized precious metal consumption with exact deposit placement.' },
          { title: 'Surface Passivation', desc: 'Anti-tarnish and oxidation protection for copper alloy leadframes. Extended shelf life without compromising electrical performance.' },
        ].map(service => (
          <div class="p-5 bg-white rounded-lg border border-steel-200/50">
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-navy-900 mb-2">{service.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-steel-400 leading-relaxed">{service.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quality -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-center">Quality Assurance & Process Control</h2>
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-4">
        {[
          '<strong class="text-steel-500">IATF 16949 certified</strong> quality management system governing all lead frame production lines.',
          'In-die vision inspection with micron-level defect detection. Cameras positioned after each forming station capture and reject deviations in real time.',
          '100% dimensional verification using automated optical inspection (AOI) systems. Critical dimensions checked against CAD nominal with SPC trending.',
          'Coplanarity measurement via laser profilometry. Every strip segment verified for flatness within specified tolerance before reel packaging.',
          'Tensile, hardness, and conductivity testing per material lot. Full traceability from raw coil to finished lead frame strip.',
          'Cleanroom-compatible packaging. Lead frames are sealed in anti-static, humidity-controlled packaging for contamination-free delivery.',
        ].map((item, i) => (
          <div class="flex gap-4 p-4 bg-steel-100/50 rounded-lg">
            <div class="w-6 h-6 bg-accent rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white text-xs font-bold shrink-0 mt-0.5">{i + 1}</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-steel-500 leading-relaxed" set:html={item}></p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-steel-100/50">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="mb-10 text-center">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        {[
          {
            q: 'What is a leadframe?',
            a: 'A leadframe is a thin metal plate that serves as the electrical interconnect between semiconductor die and external circuitry. Manufactured through high-precision stamping or etching, leadframes provide both mechanical support and conductive pathways for IC packages including QFN, SOIC, QFP, DIP, and BGA formats.',
          },
          {
            q: 'What materials are used for lead frames?',
            a: 'The most common materials for custom lead frames include copper alloys (C19400, C70250, C18150, C10200) for high conductivity applications, and iron-nickel alloys (Alloy 42) for low thermal expansion requirements. Material selection depends on the specific electrical, thermal, and mechanical requirements of the semiconductor package.',
          },
          {
            q: 'What tolerance can you achieve on stamped lead frames?',
            a: 'Our <strong class="text-steel-500">high precision lead frames</strong> achieve positional tolerance of &plusmn;0.002mm and coplanarity within 0.05mm across the full strip. These tolerances are maintained consistently across production volumes exceeding millions of units per run.',
          },
          {
            q: 'Do you support custom leadframe designs?',
            a: 'Yes. As a specialized lead frame manufacturer, we work directly with your engineering team from initial design review through tool development and full production. Our in-house tooling department can develop progressive stamping dies for any custom leadframe geometry.',
          },
        ].map(faq => (
          <details class="group bg-white rounded-lg border border-steel-200/50">
            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-5 cursor-pointer font-semibold text-navy-900 text-sm list-none">
              {faq.q}
              <span class="text-accent group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform text-lg leading-none ml-2">+</span>
            </summary>
            <div class="px-5 pb-5 text-sm text-steel-400 leading-relaxed" set:html={faq.a}></div>
          </details>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-accent">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-white mb-4">Request a Lead Frame Consultation</h2>
      <p class="text-white/80 text-lg mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Submit your drawings, material requirements, and target volumes. Our engineering team provides a DFM analysis and quotation within 24 hours.
      </p>
      <a href="/contact/" class="inline-flex items-center px-8 py-3.5 text-sm font-semibold text-accent bg-white hover:bg-steel-100 rounded transition-colors">
        Get a Quote
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Schema structured data -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Product",
    "name": "High Precision Stamped Lead Frames",
    "description": "Coplanarity-critical custom lead frames for semiconductor IC packaging. IATF 16949 certified, +/- 0.002mm tolerance, 1500+ SPM.",
    "manufacturer": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Kravzik Precision Manufacturing" },
    "category": "Lead Frames",
  })} />
</BaseLayout>
